  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">From the age 12-16 most young girls experience their Menstrual Periods for their 1st time. As a result they feel embarrassed when accidentally they find their Menses in either class,or Playground without any preventive tool to stop bleeding,Innocent and ignorant about Menstruation, they end up using grass, sponges,feathers,soil,handikerchiefs,and pieces of Paper. Some end up being mocked,nicknamed and laughed at. Your support will help provide Sustainable Sanitary Pads and reduce School dropouts</narrative>
  </description>
